   <font class="ArticleSource"><big>News Roundup:</big></font>

   <font class="ArticleHead"><big>Yo Quiero News Roundup</big></font>

   <font class="ArticleAuthorLight">&nbsp;filed by </font><font class="ArticleAuthor">Csenicier</font>

   <div align="right">
   <font class="ArticleTime">03/08/2002 01:14 PM CST</font>
   <div align="left">
   <font class="ArticleText"><BIG>Once Is Never Enough</BIG><p>We should just expect it now, honestly. If you see that one patch has been announced, expect a follow-up the next day or two:<p><B>Emergency Patch Complete Friday, March 08 2002 04:39 PST <p>The emergency patch has been completed. All servers are up and available. We apologize for any inconvenience. <p>- The EverQuest Operations Team</B><p>The servers were up Thursday, but there were huge, massive lag spikes that raised the hairs on the back of our necks. You could just feel an emergency patch coming, and sure enough, it arrived on our doorstep like a broke relative. Supposedly the patch had to do with Kael crashing during Tormax fights, but things in general just didn't seem that stable.<p>Was it inconvenient? Well, some people benefit and some loose out, depending on what kind of mobs they hunt. With the greater randomization of ubermob spawns since a few patches ago, emergency patches can have an adverse effect on scheduled activities. Yeah, yeah, poor uberguilds, boo hoo. But not everyone can stay in Sebilis all their lives, you know.<p><BIG>25 Rogue LFG</BIG><p>The denizens of Cazic Thule have been revamped on all servers.  The high-level casters pharming for their rogue twinks have been unceremoniously swept out.  They've been replaced by 50+ raiders getting owned at the zone.  Cazic Thule has always been famous for it's trains, but now those same trains are composed of level 55-60 mobs that flurry, summon, rain, and slow.  Usually the piles of corpses at the zone-in are not so well dressed.<p>The Shaman's have a <a href="http://forums.interealms.com/shaman/showthread.php?s=1f3c728c74030d33316bbf9887849361&amp;threadid=20625">nice thread</a> on the CT changes:<br><b><br>- All mobs inside now have Tae Ew as part of their name (IE Tae Ew Defender, instead of Lizard Defender) <br>- All lizards outside CT that used to be level 12ish are now level 24-30s and drops old CT loot <br>- Yard trash hits for 190 <br>- All cleric types cast Bane of Thule, AE slow <br>- Lifestealers are necros with a 350 pt Poison rain <br>- Tae Ew Warders, untargettable, guards the AoF room if you come from the TR. Haven't tried going through the sewers <br>- Exp gain seems comparable to Seb, mobs have 6k+ hps <br>- Added Raptors, see invis, faster than sow in the maz and what used to be the Tae Ew Archon temple <br>- Most yard trash has little MR and are mezzable </b><p>Thanks to Boinshar who compiled this list.<p>The Safehouse also has some of the first <a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showMessage?topicID=10177.topic">battle reports</a> coming out of the upgraded temple.  They also have an interesting <a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showMessage?topicID=10185.topic">loot spoiler thread</a>.  Say hello again to an old, and improved, favorite.  Graffe's is compiling it's own <a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showMessage?topicID=13789.topic">loot thread</a> and a Wizard shares his <a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showMessage?topicID=13631.topic">first impressions</a> of this zone.<p>Absor chimed in yesterday to allay fear of the displaced mid-level loot once found in the temple proper:<p><b>All of the stuff that you used to get out of Cazic is still available. I'm not going to give out details, that's for you to discover. But we didn't just drop the content into a dark hole, it's still out there.</b><p>Take heart, Rogue twinkers; you're still in business.<p><BIG>EQ for Free?</BIG><p>A new, ahem, <a href="http://www.player2player.net/article.php?sid=368&amp;mode=o=0">&quot;Press Release&quot;</a> took us all by surprise--and made us hungry, to boot.<p>They'll send me away for diversity training just for linking to that one...</font>
  </td>
 </tr>
